From brightly patterned tiles to intricate mosaics, sometimes beauty is right under our feet. Hundreds of thousands of Instagrammers have shared photos of eye-catching floors using the #ihavethisthingwithfloors hashtag. Featuring striking geometric designs, positive affirmations and colourful bricks, they reveal that attractive floors can appear in some pretty unlikely places â€“ such as this one in Dallas/Fort Worth international airport. The craze started one night in a bar in Amsterdam when work friends Edith Beurskens, Josha Jansen and Pien van Wijmen discovered they had something in common: they all enjoyed sharing pictures of their feet on attractive floors on Instagram. They decided to create a dedicated account where they could share their own photos and re-gram beautiful floors, using the hashtag #ihavethisthingwithfloors. Instagrammers are instructed: â€œWhen feet meet nice floors, take a selfeet.â€ Five years later, more than 845,000 photos have been shared from cities from Há»™i An to Beirut to Miami. Some are featured on the teamâ€™s original account, often coupled with an inspirational or punny caption.Guardian Cities brings together the best in urban photography on Instagram at @guardiancities. Share your shots with us on Instagram with the hashtag #guardiancities ğŸ’ƒğŸ»ğŸ’ƒğŸ»ğŸ’ƒğŸ» #ihavethisthingwithfloors photo by @beirutfloors #beirut A post shared by  I Have This Thing With Floors (@ihavethisthingwithfloors) on Aug 30, 2019 at 8:30am PDT We agree! Monday inspiration ğŸ’–ğŸ¤“ #ihavethisthingwithfloors @girlaboutohio A post shared by  I Have This Thing With Floors (@ihavethisthingwithfloors) on Jan 28, 2019 at 9:33am PST Fresh colors by @smallcrazy #ihavethisthingwithfloors A post shared by  I Have This Thing With Floors (@ihavethisthingwithfloors) on Jul 25, 2017 at 11:24pm PDT Chinese beauty ğŸ”ğŸ–¤ğŸ’¥ #ihavethisthingwithfloors by @andreannu #guangzhou #china A post shared by  I Have This Thing With Floors (@ihavethisthingwithfloors) on May 1